channel.title: Server wont go online
channel.description:
Im having problems with my server it wont go online, I have port forwarded, Changed the ips in my client with my no-ip.biz but my server won't go online. Does anyone know how to fix this? :confused:
I've used some server status checker, and it says my server is offline. Even I can't connect to my server.
I have tried 3 different No-Ip's, but that doesn't help.

item.description:

[quote=“hatem, post:9, topic:528614”][quote author=tuk link=topic=647367.msg4354086#msg4354086 date=1377163045]

Im having problems with my server it wont go online, I have port forwarded, Changed the ips in my client with my no-ip.biz but my server won’t go online.
Does anyone know how to fix this?

I’ve used some server status checker, and it says my server is offline.
Even I can’t connect to my server.

I have tried 3 different No-Ip’s, but that doesn’t help.

Your port forwarding is incorrect , re port forwarding again by using some tut appropriate to your router/modem.

Btw, It says that my no-ip is down.

Did you check if the server on buy using the website www.canyouseeme.org ?
Edit:you have to run the server before checking.

ohh, it is offline -_-
Do I have to use another port?
[/quote]
No you don’t.
i’m sure you are doing some thing wrong at port forwarding , please port forward as TCP port not Both.[/quote]

It is still offline
